<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9846> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9846" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "(X vir consul. imp. leg. scrib.). Liv. 3.35.1-9" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7470> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7470" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 471, 468, 465, 443, 439. The term pro consule (MRR 1.34, 464 B.C.), strange for this period, is taken by Sherwin-White (Roman Citizenship) 25) to refer to a federal, not a Roman, command. See also the note in Ogilvie, Comm. Livy 464-466.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/342> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #342" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.17.10, and 18.5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/321> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #321" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.13.6; Diod. 12.37.1; ILS 9338,2 ([A]grippa Menen. T. f. Lanato, T. Q[- - -]); Chr. 354 (Lanato II et Capitolino VI); Fast. Hyd. (Mallio et Capitolino); so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 95, 370f. On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/301> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #301" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.8.1, and 10.9; Diod. 12.33.1; Dion. Hal. 11.63.1; Chr. 354 (Macerino II et Barbato V); Fast. Hyd. (Macrino et Capitolino), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 7.19; Degrassi 95, 368f. Geganius relieved Ardea from Volscian attacks and celebrated a triumph (Liv. 4.9-10; Act. Tr. ([- - - -Gega]nius M. [f.-n. Mace]rinus]), Degrassi 66f., 538). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/300> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #300" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.7.10; cf. Dion. Hal. 11.62.3. See Lübker no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/288> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #288" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 3.66.1; Diod. 12.30.1; Chr. 354 (Fuso et Barbato IIII); Fast. Hyd. (Furio et Capitolino), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 95, 368f. Repelled Volscian and Aequian invaders (Liv. 3.66.1-70.15; Frontin. Str. 2.8.2 (Furius Agrippa); cf. Diod. 12.30.6); were compelled by the people to claim for Rome lands submitted to their arbitration by Ardea and Aricia (Liv. 3.71.1-72.7; Dion. Hal. 11.52). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/219> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #219" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Another tradition keeps Volscius continuously in office from 461 to 457. See these years." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/218> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #218" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued the prosecution of M. Volscius Fictor for false witness against K. Quinctius (Liv. 3.25.2-3, and 29.6; cf. Dion. Hal. 10.23.4, and 24.3). On T. Quinctius, see Lübker no. 1, on Valerius, Münzer, Gent. Val. 49, no. 45." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/181> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #181" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "[Pro consule (Liv. 3.4.10; Dion. Hal. 9.63.2). Sent with Allied forces to relieve the Consul Furius (Liv. 3.4.10-11, and 5.8-13; Dion. Hal. 9.64.3-4). See Lübker, no. 1.]" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/177> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #177" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 471, 468, 446, 443, 439 Liv. 3.2.2; Diod. 11.77.1; Fast. Cap. (F.'s name entire except Vibulanu[s II]); Dion. Hal. 9.61.1; Chr. 354 (Vivulano II et Capitolino); Cassiod.; Degrassi 24f., 91, 360f. Fabius sent an embassy to propose peace to the Aequi (Liv. 3.2.3-6). Both Consuls fought them at Algidus, then Quinctius returned to face the Aequi and hold a census (Liv. 3.2.6-3.9; Dion. Hal. 9.61.2-6). On Quinctius, see Lübker, no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/176> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #176" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. and Dion. Hal. both preserve the cognomen Capitolinus, and in Dion. Hal. Fabius' cognomen has been corrupted to {Gr}." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/172> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #172" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Assigned the land to the colonists at Antium (Liv. 3.1.6; Dion. Hal. 9.59.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/168> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #168" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 471, 465, 446, 443, 439" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/167> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #167" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Quinctius' name see 471, Consuls; on that of Servilius, see above. Diod. preserves the cognomen Structus, which may not have appeared in Fast. Cap. at all (Degrassi 91)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/159> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #159" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.56.5; Diod. 11.67.1; Dion. Hal. 9.42.3, and 43.1; Chr. 354 (Inreligiense et Barbatus); Fast. Hyd. (Sabino et Capitolino); so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi (91, 358). Claudius opposed, while Quinctius played the role of peace-maker, in the struggle leading to the passage of the Publilian law (see Tribunes of the Plebs). Claudius, in command against the Volscians, enforced discipline by using the punishment of decimation (Liv. 2.58.4-59.11; Dion. Hal. 9.50.3-7; cf. Val. Max. 9.3.5; Frontin. Str. 4.1.34; Flor. 1.17.2; App. Ital. 7; Zon. 7.17); Quinctius held command against the Aequi (Liv. 2.58.3-4, and 60.1-3; Dion. Hal. 9.50.1-2; Frontin. Str. 2.7.10). On Quinctius, see Lübker, no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/158> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #158" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The name of Claudius appears in full in Fast. Cap. on 451; that of Quinctius, based on the notices given above, is confirmed by those given under his other consular years. On his filiation, see Fast. Cap. on 460, since Cincinnatus was perhaps a brother." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10201> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10201" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Volsceis Antiatibus. MRR I.32, Itgenshorst p. 263, Rich no. 30." .
